               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Tarikh-i Firoz-Shahi by Z̤iyāʼ al-Dīn Baranī, fl. 1284-1356
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Ellis_Persian_3-item1">
                     <author key="person_2901516" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/2901516/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Z̤iyāʼ al-Dīn Baranī, fl. 1284-1356</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">ضياء الدين برنى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9583">Tarikh-i Firoz-Shahi.</title>
                     <note>F1a: A.G. Ellis 14.9.99 (also on the preceding folio, recto.) Flyleaf before text, recto: Abbott Col First flyleaf, recto: dah juz' (10 sections) and note of price. This is repeated inside the back cover. Inside front cover: armorial bookplate of James Abbott, motto 'Hesperidum'. Very possibly the famous Sir James Abbott of Abbottabad fame. See Buckland. Within the MS are a pencilled note in the hand of Simon Digby describing it and a card with 'Mr. Hast. Macsween R. Engineers' written on it. A history of the Sultans of Delhi from Balban to Firoz Shah Tughluq. This copy is defective, breaking off towards the end of the reign of Balban.</note>
                     <incipit>Hamd u thanay mar khuda'i-ra kih az akhbar u athar</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, i, pp. 505-8.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, iii, pp. 919-20.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Ethe, No 211.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
